SIMPLE: matchmaking
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Matchmaking
<hw>Match"mak`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or
process of making matches for kindling or burning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or process of trying to bring about a
marriage for others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Matchmaking</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Matchmaking
<hw>Match"mak`ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Busy in making or contriving
marriages; <as>as, a <ex>matchmaking</ex> woman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Match play</ent>⟦br⟧
